%20cost%20of%20living%20in%20Maui%20was%20extremely%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20and%20I%20had%20planned%20on%20visiting%20Japan%2C%20where%20she's%20from%2C%20right%20before%20Covid%20shut%20everything%20down.%20My%20son%20was%20born%20in%202018%20and%20my%20wife's%20family%20had%20seen%20him%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20sunset%20over%20mountains%20in%20Japan.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64aec4608ed31300199ea007%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEvans%20lives%20on%20Mukaishima%20Island%20which%20is%20about%20an%20hour%20and%20a%20half%20away%20from%20Hiroshima.%3Cp%3EAlex%20Evans%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20been%20planning%20on%20visiting%20in%202020%2C%20so%20that%20kind%20of%20got%20the%20conversation%20started%20about%20moving%20to%20Japan%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20to%20make%20up%20for%20lost%20time%2C%20giving%20our%20son%20a%20chance%20to%20spend%20time%20with%20his%20family%20there%20who%20had%20basically%20never%20really%20seen%20him.%20He%20didn't%20know%20his%20family%2C%20he%20didn't%20speak%20Japanese.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20moved%20here%20in%20June%202022.%20Once%20we%20moved%2C%20I%20realized%20pretty%20quickly%20that%20I%20wanted%20to%20stay%20long%20term.%20More%20recently%20%E2%80%94%20probably%20within%20the%20last%20month%20or%20so%20%E2%80%94%20my%20wife%20started%20to%20feel%20the%20same%20way.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMy%20rent%20is%20%241%2C800%20less%20than%20it%20was%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20own%20a%20medical%20writing%20business%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fsoutheasttravelguide.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etravel%20site%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20built%20that%20up%20while%20I%20was%20working%20as%20a%20pharmacist%20in%20the%20US%2C%20so%20now%20I'm%20able%20to%20work%20from%20anywhere.%20I%20also%20work%20at%20a%20local%20bike%20shop%2C%20which%20is%20primarily%20so%20I'm%20immersed%20in%20an%20all-Japanese%20environment.%20With%20language%20learning%2C%20there's%20only%20so%20much%20you%20can%20learn%20from%20sitting%20in%20the%20house%20looking%20at%20books%20and%20listening%20to%20podcasts.%20And%20I%20love%20cycling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hourly%20rate%20is%20probably%20below%20what%20would%20be%20minimum%20wage%20in%20the%20US%2C%20but%20it's%20only%20two%20days%20a%20week.%20I%20essentially%20see%20it%20as%20a%20way%20to%20learn%20Japanese%20in%20a%20fun%20environment%20since%20I%20like%20bikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221393%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20riding%20a%20bike.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64aec28a8ed31300199e9f62%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221045%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEvans%20taking%20a%20rental%20bike%20from%20the%20shop%20out%20for%20a%20spin.%3Cp%3EAlex%20Evans%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20renting%20a%20three-bedroom%20house%20on%20Mukaishima%20Island.%20It's%20not%20typical%20to%20have%20two%20baths%2C%20so%20it%20is%20a%20one-bath.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20area%20is%20really%20cheap.%20I'm%20not%20in%20Hiroshima%20City%2C%20I'm%20in%20an%20island%20city%2C%20so%20the%20prices%20in%20Hiroshima%20City%20would%20be%20very%20different.%20The%20rent%20here%20is%2065%2C000%20yen%20per%20month%2C%20or%20about%20%24463.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Jacksonville%2C%20I%20had%20a%20mortgage%20that%20was%20%242%2C000%20a%20month.%20We%20sold%20that%20house%20about%20a%20year%20before%20moving%20to%20Japan%20and%20rented%20for%20a%20year%20because%20it%20felt%20easier.%20By%20the%20time%20you%20count%20the%20fees%20with%20the%20apartment%20and%20everything%2C%20I%20think%20we%20were%20at%20%242%2C300%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20looking%20at%20buying%20a%20house%2C%20and%20we%20have%20a%20house%20already%20that%20a%20neighbor%20is%20going%20to%20sell%20us.%20Right%20now%20we're%20renting%20just%20one%20street%20over%20while%20that's%20all%20getting%20sorted%20out.%20Between%20the%20purchase%20price%20and%20interest%2C%20we're%20looking%20at%20around%2075%2C000-80%2C000%20yen%20a%20month.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EExpenses%20for%20my%20family%20are%20significantly%20cheaper%20in%20Japan%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ride%20my%20bike%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20places%2C%20but%20we%20do%20own%20a%20car.%20We%20bought%20it%20for%20about%20%244%2C000.%20I%20would%20say%20gas%20is%20definitely%20more%20expensive%20here.%20They%20price%20it%20in%20liters%2C%20and%20the%20going%20rate%20might%20be%20170%20yen%20per%20liter%20%E2%80%94%20and%20there's%20about%20four%20liters%20in%20a%20gallon.%20So%20it%20is%20more%20expensive%20than%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFood%20is%20far%20cheaper%20for%20most%20things%2C%20especially%20if%20you%20eat%20the%20food%20that%20locals%20eat.%20I%20could%20go%20down%20to%20the%20store%20now%20and%20get%20tofu%20for%20probably%2035%20yen%20a%20pack%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20about%2020%20cents%20a%20pack.%20I%20can%20get%20bread%20for%20about%20a%20dollar%2C%20and%20produce%20is%20inexpensive.%20Overall%2C%20groceries%20might%20be%20a%20third%20of%20what%20they%20are%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20my%20son%2C%20we%20were%20paying%20%24750%20to%20%24800%20a%20month%20for%20his%20daycare%20in%20the%20US%2C%20which%20is%20significantly%20cheaper%20than%20in%20the%20US.%20In%20Japan%2C%20the%20school%20is%20heavily%20subsidized%20by%20the%20government.%20There%20are%20some%20fees%2C%20but%20I%20think%20we%20pay%20%2435%20to%20%2440%20a%20month%20for%20his%20lunch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20just%20blown%20away%20seeing%20him%20get%20grilled%20salmon%20and%20rice%20for%20lunch%20in%20Japan.%20It's%20a%20beautiful%20school.%20It%20looks%20like%20the%20kind%20of%20private%20school%20you%20would%20have%20to%20pay%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20for%20your%20child%20to%20go%20to%20in%20the%20US%2C%20but%20it's%20just%20a%20public%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20view%20of%20a%20city%20in%20Japan%20from%20atop%20a%20mountain.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64aec4b78ed31300199ea030%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENearly%20everything%20except%20gas%20is%20cheaper%20in%20Japan%2C%20Evans%20said.%3Cp%3EAlex%20Evans%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20that%20kind%20of%20surprised%20me%20and%20is%20a%20major%20reason%20for%20not%20wanting%20to%20move%20back%20to%20the%20US%20is%20healthcare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20pharmacist%2C%20I%20know%C2%A0a%20lot%20about%20fighting%20the%20insurance%20companies%20and%20dealing%20with%20all%20of%20the%20dysfunction%20in%20the%20US%20healthcare%20system.%20This%20is%20the%20first%20time%20I've%20ever%20been%20a%20patient%20before%20in%20a%20universal%20healthcare%20system.%20And%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20lie%2C%20it%20feels%20really%20good.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20one%20insurance%20card%2C%20and%20we%20went%20to%20the%20town%20hall%20to%20get%20it.%20Basically%20you%20just%20show%20that%20you're%20a%20resident%20of%20that%20town%20and%20you%20get%20handed%20your%20insurance%20card.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20show%20the%20same%20card%20to%20the%20dentist%2C%20the%20doctor%20and%20the%20eye%20doctor.%20There%20is%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20vision%20and%20dental%2C%20there's%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20deductibles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20feel%20a%20lot%20safer%20here%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20initial%20reason%20for%20moving%20was%20for%20family%20reasons%2C%20but%20pretty%20quickly%20after%20getting%20here%2C%20I%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20other%20reasons.%20The%20first%20thing%20was%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20very%20concerned%20about%20gun%20violence%20in%20the%20US%2C%20which%20is%20almost%20non-existent%20in%20Japan.%20My%20wife%20was%20still%20saying%20she%20wanted%20to%20go%20back%20to%20the%20US%2C%20but%20after%20the%20Nashville%20school%20shooting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fnashville-shooting-video-shows-kids-holding-hands-evacuating-covenant-school-2023-3%3F_gl%3D1*13x6zzx*_ga*NjI0Njg2MTQxLjE2NDMwNTA4NDk.*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTY4OTE3Mzg1My4xMjAyLjEuMTY4OTE3Mzg4MS4zMi4wLjA.%5C%22%3Eearlier%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20I%20was%20extremely%20upset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20upset%20for%20the%20families%20of%20those%20children%20and%20I%20was%20very%20upset%20because%20I%20have%20a%20five%20year%20old%20child%20and%20we%20were%20getting%20ready%20to%20plan%20a%20move%20back%20to%20the%20US%20where%20he%20was%20going%20to%20potentially%20be%20in%20that.%20So%20the%20school%20shootings%20and%20mass%20shootings%20in%20general%20are%20something%20that%20are%20a%20major%20reason%20for%20me%20not%20wanting%20to%20move%20back.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20residential%20street%20in%20Japan.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64aec34e94be880019f39811%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEvans%20feels%20safer%20in%20his%20neighborhood%20than%20he%20did%20in%20the%20US.%3Cp%3EAlex%20Evans%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20many%20Americans%20are%20frustrated%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20different%20aspects%20of%20the%20US.%20I%20think%20maybe%20that's%20the%20one%20thing%20most%20Americans%20can%20agree%20on%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20just%20people%20can't%20agree%20on%20what%20to%20do%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20really%20feel%20the%20need%20to%20lock%20my%20doors%20here%20%E2%80%94%20I%20don't%20know%20if%20this%20is%20true%20for%20all%20of%20Japan%20because%20I'm%20in%20a%20more%20rural%20area%20on%20an%20island%20%E2%80%94%20but%20this%20has%20been%20my%20experience.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20when%20I%20ride%20my%20bike%20I%20don't%20even%20lock%20it%20when%20I