%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689245893000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64afe044c22d1a0019453fd5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcharacterai-artificial-intelligence-chatbot-mimics-mario-elon-musk-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Character.AI%20has%20around%20a%20dozen%20versions%20of%20Elon%20Musk%20that%20users%20can%20chat%20with%2C%20including%20a%20%26quot%3Bkind%2C%20gassy%2C%20proud%26quot%3B%20unicorn.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bnolan%40insider.com%20(Beatrice%20Nolan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcharacterai-artificial-intelligence-chatbot-mimics-mario-elon-musk-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Salman%20Rushdie%20Speaks%20Of%20%5C%22Crazy%20Dreams%5C%22%20About%20Knife%20Attack%20In%20New%20York%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESalman%20Rushdie%20has%20spoken%20for%20the%20first%20time%20about%20having%20%26quot%3Bcrazy%20dreams%26quot%3B%20following%20the%20near-fatal%20knife%20attack%20on%20him%20in%20New%20York%20in%20August%20last%20year%2C%20which%20has%20left%20the%20Mumbai-born%20author%20blind%20in%20one%20eye%2C%20and%20working%20with%20a%20therapist%20to%20help%20him%20process%20the%20mental%20impact%20of%20the%20trauma.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2076-year-old%20Booker%20Prize-winning%20author%20was%20on%20stage%20almost%20a%20year%20ago%20when%20he%20was%20stabbed%20up%20to%2010%20times%20by%20the%20suspect%20Hadi%20Matar%2C%20who%20is%20being%20held%20in%20prison%20for%20attempted%20murder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20the%20BBC%20this%20week%2C%20Rushdie%20said%20he%20was%20in%20%26quot%3Btwo%20minds%26quot%3B%20about%20whether%20to%20face%20his%20alleged%20attacker%2C%20who%20has%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%2C%20in%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20a%20very%20good%20therapist%20who%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20to%20do.%20I%20have%20crazy%20dreams%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20British-American%20novelist%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20he%20changes%20his%20plea%20to%20guilty%20then%20actually%20there's%20not%20a%20trial%2C%20there's%20just%20a%20sentencing%2C%20and%20it%20may%20well%20be%20that%20then%20my%20presence%20isn't%20required.%20I'm%20in%20two%20minds%20about%20it.%20There's%20one%20bit%20of%20me%20that%20actually%20wants%20to%20go%20and%20stand%20on%20the%20court%20and%20look%20at%20him%20and%20there's%20another%20bit%20of%20me%20that%20just%20can't%20be%20bothered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20a%20very%20high%20opinion%20of%20him.%20And%20I%20think%20what%20is%20important%20to%20me%20now%20is%20that%20you're%20able%20to%20find%20life%20continuing.%20I'm%20more%20engaged%20with%20the%20business%20of%2C%20you%20know%2C%20getting%20on%20with%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20when%20asked%20if%20he%20plans%20to%20attend%20Matar's%20trial%20later%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20injuries%20from%20the%20attack%20resulted%20in%20damage%20to%20his%20liver%2C%20loss%20of%20vision%20in%20one%20eye%20and%20a%20paralysed%20hand%20caused%20by%20nerve%20damage%20to%20his%20arm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20human%20body%20has%20an%20amazing%20capacity%20to%20heal.%20And%20so%20I'm%20fortunate%20to%20be%20well%20on%20that%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20author%20of%20'Midnight's%20Children'%20who%20says%20he%20feels%20physically%20%26quot%3Bmore%20or%20less%20OK%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20put%20on%20a%20ventilator%20and%20spent%20six%20weeks%20in%20hospital%20after%20being%20stabbed%20up%20to%2010%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERushdie%20is%20now%20writing%20a%20book%20about%20the%20near-fatal%20stabbing%20incident%20as%20a%20means%20of%20processing%20what%20he%20has%20been%20through.%20In%20the%20virtual%20interview%2C%20he%20told%20the%20BBC%20it%20won't%20be%20more%20than%20a%20%26quot%3Bcouple%20of%20hundred%20pages%26q