e%20flood%20situation%20but%20assured%20that%20the%20water%20supply%20in%20these%20areas%20will%20restart%20by%20tomorrow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRight%20now%20the%20water%20level%20crossed%20208.6%20metre.%20It%20was%20not%20expected%20that%20the%20water%20would%20reach%20this%20level.%20Three%20of%20our%20water%20treatment%20plants%20have%20been%20shut%20down%20because%20water%20has%20entered%20the%20pump.%20After%20the%20water%20recedes%2C%20the%20machines%20will%20be%20dried%20and%20then%20started%20again%20so%20that%20current%20is%20generated.%20About%2025%20per%20cent%20water%20supply%20has%20been%20affected.%20We%20will%20be%20able%20to%20start%20water%20supply%20by%20tomorrow%20evening%26quot%3B%2C%20he%20told%20ANI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Delhi's%20Directorate%20of%20Education%20has%20ordered%20all%20government%20and%20private%20schools%20in%20low-lying%20areas%20to%20close%20immediately%20where%20there%20is%20a%20danger%20of%20flood%20without%20waiting%20for%20orders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20view%20of%20the%20flood%20situation%20in%20Delhi%2C%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Education%2C%20Government%20of%20Delhi%20has%20ordered%20all%20government%20and%20private%20schools%20in%20low-lying%20areas%20to%20close%20immediately%20without%20waiting%20for%20orders%20where%20there%20is%20a%20danger%20of%20flood%26quot%3B%2C%20said%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChandgi%20Ram%20Akhada%20Chowk%20area%20of%20Delhi%20on%20Thursday%20witnessed%20severe%20flooding%20due%20to%20rise%20in%20the%20Yamuna%20waters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20low-lying%20areas%20of%20the%20city%20are%20still%20under%20water%20as%20the%20water%20level%20in%20Yamuna%20continues%20to%20rise%20following%20heavy%20rainfall%20and%20the%20release%20of%20water%20from%20the%20Hathnikund%20Barrage%20in%20neighbouring%20Haryana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20the%20rise%20in%20the%20water%20level%20of%20Yamuna%20and%20the%20resultant%20inundation%20of%20low-lying%20areas%2C%20traffic%20movement%20has%20been%20impaired%20in%20several%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20according%20to%20official%20inputs%2C%20the%20movement%20of%20commercial%20vehicles%20will%20be%20regulated%20as%20non-destined%20commercial%20vehicles%20won't%20be%20allowed%20to%20enter%20Delhi%20and%20will%20be%20diverted%20to%20the%20Eastern%20and%20Western%20Peripheral%20Expressways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommercial%20vehicles%20will%20be%20diverted%20from%20Mukarba%20Chowk%2C%20Sarai%20Kale%20Khan%2C%20Ghazipur%20border%2C%20and%20from%20Akshardham%20towards%20DND.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20officials%20further%20said%20no%20commercial%20vehicles%20will%20be%20allowed%20between%20Mukarba%20Chowk%20and%20Wazirabad%20Bridge%2C%20Sarai%20Kale%20Khan%20and%20IP%20Flyover%2C%20and%20Akshardham%20and%20Sarai%20Kale%20Khan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20India%20Meteorological%20Department%20(IMD)%20has%20forecasted%20light%20to%20moderate%20intensity%20rain%20in%20South-West%20Delhi%20and%20adjoining%20areas%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThunderstorm%20with%20light%20to%20moderate%20intensity%20rain%20would%20occur%20over%20and%20adjoining%20areas%20of%20isolated%20places%20of%20South-West%20Delhi%2C%20South%20Delhi%20(Chhattarpur%2C%20IGNOU%2C%20Ayanagar%2C%20Deramandi)%20and%20NCR%20(Gurugram%2C%20Manesar)%2C%20Sikandrabad%2C%20Bulandshahar%2C%20Khurja%2C%20Pahasu%20(U.P.)%20during%20next%202%20hours%26quot%3B%2C%20IMD%20said%20in%20a%20tweet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689240180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fenqgiu8g_delhi-flood_625x300_13_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdont-leave-house-if-arvind-kejriwal-makes-a-request-amid-delhi-flooding-4203470%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Due%20to%20the%20rise%20in%20the%20water%20level%20of%20Yamuna%2C%20traffic%20movement%20has%20been%20severely%20hit%20in%20several%20parts%20of%20Delhi.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdont-leave-house-if-arvind-kejriwal-makes-a-request-amid-delhi-flooding-4203470%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdont-leave-house-if-arvind-kejriwal-makes-a-request-amid-delhi-flooding-4203470%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdont-leave-house-if-arvind-kejriwal-makes-a-request-amid-delhi-flooding-4203470%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22More%20Than%20Half%20The%20World's%20Oceans%20Have%20Changed%20Colour.%20Read%20Why%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20colour%20of%20over%2056%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20world's%20oceans%2C%20larger%20than%20Earth's%20total%20land%20expanse%2C%20has%20changed%20significantly%20over%20the%20last%20two%20decades%20and%20human-caused%20climate%20change%20is%20likely%20the%20driver%2C%20according%20to%20researchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20colour%20changes%2C%20subtle%20to%20the%20human%20eye%2C%20cannot%20be%20explained%20by%20natural%2C%20year-to-year%20variability%20alone%2C%20the%20researchers%20from%20the%20Massachusetts%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20(MIT)%2C%20US%2C%20and%20other%20institutes%20write%20in%20their%20paper%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Nature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOcean%20colour%2C%20a%20literal%20reflection%20of%20the%20life%20and%20materials%20in%20its%20waters%2C%20in%20regions%20near%20the%20equator%20was%20found%20to%20have%20steadily%20turned%20greener%20over%20time%2C%20indicating%20changes%20in%20the%20ecosystems%20within%20the%20surface%20oceans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20green%20colour%20of%20the%20ocean%20waters%20comes%20from%20the%20green%20pigment%20chlorophyll%20present%20in%20phytoplankton%2C%20the%20plant-like%20microbes%20abundant%20in%20upper%20ocean.%20Scientists%20are%2C%20therefore%2C%20keen%20to%20monitor%20phytoplankton%20to%20see%20their%20response%20to%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20authors%20of%20this%20study%20showed%20through%20previous%20studies%20that%20it%20would%20take%2030%20years%20of%20tracking%20chlorophyll%20changes%20before%20climate-change-driven%20trends%20would%20show%2C%20because%20natural%2C%20annual%20variations%20in%20chlorophyll%20would%20overwhelm%20those%20influenced%20by%20human%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202019%20paper%2C%20study%20co-author%20Stephanie%20Dutkiewicz%20and%20her%20colleagues%20showed%20that%20monitoring%20other%20ocean%20colours%2C%20whose%20annual%20variations%20are%20much%20smaller%20than%20those%20of%20chlorophyll%2C%20would%20convey%20more%20clear%20signals%20of%20climate-change-driven%20changes%20and%20that%20they%20might%20even%20be%20apparent%20in%2020%20years%2C%20rather%20than%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20worth%20looking%20at%20the%20whole%20spectrum%2C%20rather%20than%20just%20trying%20to%20estimate%20one%20number%20from%20bits%20of%20the%20spectrum%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20lead%20author%20B.%20B.%20Cael%20of%20the%20National%20Oceanography%20Center.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECael%20and%20team%20then%20statistically%20analysed%20all%20the%20seven%20ocean%20colours%20recorded%20by%20satellite%20observations%20from%202002%20to%202022%20together.%20He%20initially%20studied%20the%20colours'%20natural%20variations%20by%20seeing%20how%20they%20changed%20regionally%20in%20a%20given%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20then%20observed%20how%20these%20annual%20variations%20changed%20over%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%20climate%20change's%20contribution%20to%20all%20these%20changes%2C%20he%20used%20Dutkiewicz's%202019%20model%20to%20simulate%20the%20Earth's%20oceans%20under%20two%20scenarios%20-%20one%20with%20greenhouse%20gases%20and%20the%20other%20without%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20greenhouse-gas%20model%20predicted%20changes%20to%20the%20colour%20of%20about%2050%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20world's%20surface%20oceans%20in%20under%2020%20years%20-%20close%20to%20Cael's%20conclusions%20from%20his%20real-world%20satellite%20data%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20suggests%20that%20the%20trends%20we%20observe%20are%20not%20a%20random%20variation%20in%20the%20Earth%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cael.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20consistent%20with%20anthropogenic%20climate%20change.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20been%20running%20simulations%20that%20have%20been%20telling%20me%20for%20years%20that%20these%20changes%20in%20ocean%20colour%20are%20going%20to%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dutkiewicz%2C%20senior%20research%20scientist%20in%20MIT's%20Department%20of%20Earth%2C%20Atmospheric%20and%20Planetary%20Sciences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20actually%20see%20it%20happening%20for%20real%20is%20not%20surprising%2C%20but%20frightening.%20And%20these%20changes%20are%20consistent%20with%20man-induced%20changes%20to%20our%20climate%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689239820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2F5t2ebq0c_ocean-generic-ocean-colour-change-generic-pixabay_625x300_13_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fmore-than-half-the-worlds-oceans-have-changed-colour-read-why-4203238%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20colour%20of%20over%2056%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20world's%20oceans%2C%20larger%20than%20Earth's%20total%20land%20expanse%2C%20has%20changed%20significantly%20over%20the%20last%20two%20decades%20and%20human-caused%20climate%20change%20is%20likely%20the%20drive