ging-yamuna-flowing-at-record-level-spills-onto-streets-in-delhi-%2F607241.html%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20parts%20of%20the%20city%20on%20the%20banks%20of%20the%20river%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20Monastery%20Market%2C%20Yamuna%20Bazar%2C%20Geeta%20Ghat%20and%20the%20stretch%20from%20Majnu%20Ka%20Tilla%20to%20Wazirabad%20%E2%80%93%20were%20already%20flooded%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2FDelhi%2Fyamuna-water-level-breaches-60-year-record-kejriwal-seeks-centres-help%2Farticle67073258.ece%5C%22%3Enews%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20of%20Wednesday%20night%2C%20more%20than%2016%2C000%20people%20were%20evacuated%20from%20low-lying%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20July%2012%2C%20Delhi%20Police%20had%20imposed%20Section%20144%20under%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20which%20prohibits%20the%20gathering%20of%20four%20or%20more%20people%2C%20in%20parts%20of%20the%20city%20that%20are%20prone%20to%20floods.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689239245000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F13143627%2FDSC09659.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fyamuna-continues-to-rise-beyond-record-high-delhi-secretariat-housing-offices-flooded%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22More%20than%2016%2C000%20people%20have%20already%20been%20evacuated%20as%20of%20Wednesday%20night%2C%20as%20per%20reports.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fyamuna-continues-to-rise-beyond-record-high-delhi-secretariat-housing-offices-flooded%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20NATO's%20Remarkable%20Journey%20-%2020th%20Century%20Alliance%20In%2021st%20Century%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EBefore%20Russia%20launched%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20last%20year%2C%20the%20North%20Atlantic%20Treaty%20Organization%20(NATO)%20was%20widely%20considered%20to%20be%20a%20relic%20of%20the%20past.%20It%20used%20to%20be%20in%20the%20news%20more%20for%20the%20problems%20of%20cohesion%20it%20was%20encountering%20ever%20since%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%20than%20for%20the%20forward-looking%20agenda%20of%20its%20members.%20In%20fact%2C%20American%20political%20scientist%20John%20Mearsheimer%20had%20questioned%20the%20logic%20of%20America's%20continued%20presence%20in%20NATO%20after%20the%20demise%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20and%20had%20predicted%20that%20slowly%2C%20but%20surely%2C%20NATO%20would%20move%20towards%20oblivion.%20If%20the%20threat%20against%20which%20the%20alliance%20was%20crafted%2C%20the%20logic%20went%2C%20no%20longer%20existed%2C%20what%20was%20the%20point%20of%20the%20alliance%20itself%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20sense%20of%20purpose%20that%20NATO%20had%20seemingly%20lost%20after%201990%20is%20fast%20re-emerging%20as%20Russian%20aggression%20against%20Ukraine%20seems%20to%20have%20produced%20more%20unity%20than%20would%20have%20been%20anticipated%20just%20a%20year%20back.%20Russia%20has%20ostensibly%20moved%20against%20Ukraine%20to%20send%20out%20a%20message%20to%20NATO%20about%20its%20expansion%20to%20its%20backyard.%20But%20as%20this%20week's%20NATO%20summit%20in%20Vilnius%2C%20Lithuania%20underscored%2C%20there%20is%20a%20now%20a%20new%20momentum%20in%20the%20process%20of%20NATO%20expansion%20with%20Finland%20joining%20the%20alliance%20in%20April%20and%20Sweden%20all%20set%20to%20become%20the%20newest%20member%20after%20Turkey's%20Erdogan%20dropped%20his%20opposition%20to%20its%20membership.%20Though%20many%20in%20Ukraine%20would%20have%20been%20disappointed%2C%20even%20Ukraine's%20potential%20candidacy%20for%20the%20NATO%20was%20accelerated%20with%20the%20alliance%20deciding%20to%20waive%20off%20the%20Membership%20Action%20Plan%20(MAP).%20Though%20NATO%20members%20did%20not%20specify%20a%20timeframe%2C%20they%20recognized%20the%20need%20to%20move%20faster%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20Ukraine's%20NATO%20membership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelensky%20had%20criticised%20the%20%26quot%3Bunprecedented%20and%20absurd%26quot%3B%20delay%20to%20accession%2C%20suggesting%20that%20there%20seemed%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bno%20readiness%26quot%3B%20to%20invite%20Ukraine%20to%20NATO.%20But%20by%20the%20time%20the%20summit%20concluded%2C%20there%20were%20strong%20signals%20from%20major%20powers%20that%20support%20for%20Ukraine%20remains%20steadfast%20within%20the%20alliance.%20The%20G-7%20nations%20came%20out%20with%20a%20rather%20expansive%20framework%20that%20guarantees%20long%20term%20support%20for%20Ukraine%20by%20ensuring%20%26quot%3Ba%20sustainable%20force%20capable%20of%20defending%20Ukraine%20now%20and%20deterring%20Russian%20aggression%20in%20the%20future%26quot%3B%20even%20as%20it%20seeks%20to%20help%20Kyiv%20with%20%26quot%3Bthe%20good%20governance%20necessary%20to%20advance%20towards%20its%20Euro-Atlantic%20aspirations.%26quot%3B%20This%20commitment%20is%20not%20only%20about%20ensuring%20that%20Ukraine's%20immediate%20security%20needs%20are%20met%20but%20also%20about%20the%20long%20term%20economic%20viability%20of%20the%20war-torn%20nation.%20With%20the%20declaration%20underlining%20%26quot%3Bthe%20need%20for%20the%20establishment%20of%20an%20international%20mechanism%20for%20reparation%20of%20damages%2C%20loss%20or%20injury%20caused%20by%20Russian%20aggression%2C%26quot%3B%20Moscow's%20reaction%20was%20swift%2C%20calling%20the%20G-7%20security%20guarantees%20%26quot%3Berroneous%20and%20dangerous.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20package%20of%20guarantees%20and%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20NATO-Ukraine%20Council%20is%20intended%20as%20a%20signal%20to%20both%20Ukraine%20and%20Russia.%20To%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20message%20is%20clear%20that%20its%20long%20term%20security%20is%20now%20the%20responsibility%20of%20its%20allies%20and%20they%20are%20invested%20in%20it.%20Kyiv's%20allies%20are%20willing%20to%20hand-hold%20Ukraine%20as%20it%20seeks%20a%20path%20to%20NATO%20membership.%20It%20won't%20come%20soon%20but%20the%20commitment%20is%20clear.%20To%20Russia%2C%20the%20message%20is%20also%20equally%20categorical%20that%20Ukraine%20may%20not%20be%20a%20NATO%20member%20today%20but%20tomorrow%20is%20another%20day.%20And%20with%20Sweden%20and%20Finland%20as%20part%20of%20the%20alliance%2C%20the%20absurdity%20of%20Russia's%20strategic%20objective%20of%20preventing%20NATO's%20expansion%20has%20been%20exposed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20should%20be%20worrying%20for%20Moscow%20is%20how%20readily%20Turkish%20President%20Recep%20Tayyip%20Erdogan%20agreed%20to%20Sweden's%20bid%20for%20NATO%20after%20initially%20raising%20several%20obstacles.%20After%20Erdogan's%20change%20of%20heart%2C%20the%20Biden%20Administration%20moved%20quickly%20to%20suggest%20that%20the%20transfer%20of%20F-16%20fighter%20jets%20is%20on%20its%20way%2C%20something%20that%20Turkey%20has%20been%20demanding%20for%20years.%20Last%20week%20Erdogan%20met%20Zelensky%20in%20Istanbul%2C%20where%20he%20came%20out%20in%20support%20of%20Ukrainian%20independence%20and%20it%20led%20to%20the%20return%20to%20Ukraine%20of%20five%20former%20military%20commanders%20who%20had%20fought%20in%20the%20battle%20over%20Mariupol.%20Turkey%20has%20been%20a%20major%20interlocutor%20for%20Russia%20so%20far%20but%20now%2C%20with%20Erdogan%20trying%20to%20mend%20fences%20with%20the%20West%20post%20his%20re-election%20for%20another%20five%20years%2C%20Moscow's%20challenge%20on%20the%20global%20stage%20is%20only%20likely%20to%20increase.%20Not%20surprisingly%2C%20the%20initial%20reaction%20from%20Russia%20has%20been%20highly%20critical%20with%20some%20officials%20reportedly%20suggesting%20that%20Turkey%20is%20turning%20into%20an%20%26quot%3Bunfriendly%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NATO%20summit%20in%20Lithuania%20is%20a%20high%20point%20for%20Biden's%20diplomatic%20footprint.%20He%20has%20managed%20to%20keep%20the%20alliance%20intact%20despite%20some%20differences%20over%20the%20issue%20of%20cluster%20munitions%20and%20the%20expansion%20of%20NATO%20is%20a%20reminder%20that%20American%20leadership%20remains%20a%20precondition%20for%20western%20unity%20on%20global%20matters.%20But%20more%20than%20Russia%2C%20it%20is%20Beijing%20that%20should%20be%20concerned%20about%20the%20growing%20resoluteness%20in%20NATO%20vis-a-vis%20China%20with%20the%20latest%20communique%20underlining%20the%20challenge%20posed%20by%20China%20to%20the%20alliance's%20interests%2C%20security%20and%20values%20with%20its%20%26quot%3Bstated%20ambitions%20and%20coercive%20policies.%26quot%3B%20It%20was%20last%20year%20that%20NATO%20had%20released%20its%20Strategic%20Concept%20that%20for%20the%20first%20time%20talked%20of%20risks%20posed%20by%20Chinese%20ambitions%20with%20Asia-Pacific%20becoming%20important%20for%20the%20alliance%20in%20an%20interconnected%20world.%20With%20the%20presence%20of%20Australian%20Prime%20Minister%20Anthony%20Albanese%2C%20Japanese%20Prime%20Minister%20Fumio%20Kishida%2C%20New%20Zealand%20Prime%20Minister%20Chris%20Hipkins%20and%20South%20Korean%20President%20Yoon%20Suk-yeol%20at%20this%20year's%20NATO%20summit%2C%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20the%20focus%20of%20NATO%20is%20sharpening%20on%20the%20Indo-Pacific.%20Chinese%20concerns%20are%20evident%20in%20its%20reaction%20expressed%20in%20a%20warning%20that%20%26quot%3Bany%20act%20that%20jeopardises%20China's%20legitimate%20rights%20and%20interests%20will%20be%20met%20with%20a%20resolute%20response.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20world%20order%20undergoes%20a%20transformation%2C%20it%20is%20natural%20that%20alliances%20created%20for%20the%2020th%20century%20will%20have%20to%20adapt%20to%2021st%20century%20realities.%20NATO%20has%20shown%20great%20agility%20since%20its%20existence%20and%20it%20is%20now%20entering%20the%20geopolitical%20space%20that%20India%20inhabits.%20For%20New%20Delhi%2C%20ignoring%20this%20re