have%20been%20languishing%20for%20almost%2030%20years.%20Our%20direction%20was%20passed%20in%20May%202022%20to%20decide%20applications%20of%20the%20petitioners%20before%20us%20within%20three%20months%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%2C%20which%20also%20included%20Justice%20Dipankar%20Datta%2C%20told%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20additional%20advocate%20general%2C%20Ardhendumauli%20Kumar%20Prasad%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20directed%20the%20state%20home%20department%E2%80%99s%20principal%20secretary%20to%20remain%20present%20in%20the%20court%20on%20August%2029%20if%20the%20authorities%20fail%20to%20dispose%20of%20all%20pending%20applications%20within%20four%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20was%20livid%20that%20the%20UP%20government%20was%20yet%20to%20act%20on%20its%20direction%2C%20given%20on%20May%2016%2C%202022%2C%20asking%20the%20authorities%20to%20take%20a%20final%20call%20within%20three%20months.%20In%20its%20May%202022%20order%2C%20the%20court%20had%20taken%20note%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20all%20the%20petitioners%2C%20lodged%20in%20Bareilly%E2%80%99s%20Central%20Jail%2C%20had%20completed%20more%20than%2014%20years%20of%20their%20actual%20sentence%20without%20remission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20had%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20remission%20policy%20along%20with%20several%20directives%20passed%20by%20the%20apex%20court%20obligate%20the%20state%20government%20to%20dispose%20off%20a%20prisoners%20remission%20plea%20within%20three%20months%20of%20it%20becoming%20eligible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20amount%20of%20disrespect%20your%20authorities%20are%20showing%2C%20we%20think%20we%20will%20have%20to%20take%20some%20harsh%20steps.%20Your%20officers%20have%20scant%20respect%20for%20the%20orders%20of%20the%20court.%20That%E2%80%99s%20what%20is%20happening%20in%20your%20state%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20commented.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%2042%20